race.comment: Found it tough to go past the Derby winner OBSERVER (1). There are obvious knocks on him resuming - 1400m is short of his best, he has G1 targets down the road and he gives all of these weight, but he probably should've won a Caulfield Guineas over 1600m last campaign and he might just be too classy for these. PLANET RED (3) did beat OBSERVER home in the Caulfield Guineas with a strong second to Autumn Boy. Not sure where he gets to from the draw, and he hasn't exactly caught the eye at the jumpouts, but on form he's a huge chance. DAVIDA (12) is the tricky one. She's won two in a row and will have plenty of fitness despite being five weeks between runs. She beat the older horses in good time at Geelong when last seen and could look to pinch this. MASTER OF THE AIR (5) resumes. He'll want further but can be hitting the line strongly. BUCCLEUCH (2) had things against fresh - he's better than that and also boasts a win over OBSERVER as a 2yo.
